  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why can't I change my profile picture on Quora via my phone?",
  "response": "If you're having trouble changing your profile picture on Quora using your phone, there could be several reasons for this issue. Here are some common causes and potential solutions:\n\n1. **App Version**: Ensure that you're using the latest version of the Quora app. Outdated versions may have bugs or missing features. Go to your app store, check for updates, and install the latest version if available.\n\n2. **Internet Connection**: A stable internet connection is required to upload a profile picture. Check your connection and try again.\n\n3. **Image File**: The image file you're trying to upload may be too large or in an unsupported format. Try resizing the image or converting it to a common format like JPEG or PNG.\n\n4. **App Permissions**: The Quora app needs permission to access your photos. Check your phone's settings to ensure that Quora has the necessary permissions.\n\n5. **Cache and Data**: Sometimes, clearing the app's cache and data can resolve issues. Go to your phone's settings, find the Quora app, and clear its cache and data. Note that this will log you out, so you'll need to log back in.\n\n6. **Platform-Specific Issues**: There might be a temporary glitch or bug affecting the Quora app on your specific device or operating system. If none of the above solutions work, you can try using the Quora website through your phone's browser to change your profile picture.\n\nIf you continue to experience issues, you may want to reach out to Quora's support team for further assistance.",
